	 whether you are just starting out or are an experienced journaler. In thi
	s warm and welcoming environment\, you will be encouraged to experiment an
	d find your voice. In each session we will gather for introductions and br
	ief guidance\, and then head out into Garden to journal and come back toge
	ther to share experiences.   \n\nPlease bring a dedicated journal and some
	thing to write with. We will meet at 9am the first Saturday of January-Nov
	ember 2026. Registration is recommended but not required. REGISTER NOW.  \
	n\nThis free adult program is facilitated by Anne Dziok\, Adult Education 
	Program Manager. Anne is a practicing multi-media artist who shows her wor
	k regionally.    \n\nEmail us  with questions.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity
	.com/events/#/details/journaling-the-garden/17658183/2026-03-07T00\n\nFrom
	 SEAtoday - Community & Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/journaling-the-garden/176
	58183/2026-03-07T00
LOCATION:Sharp Cabin\, 12001 Main St\, Bellevue\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-community
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Community & Civic
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
