BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:kdOYARv0exMP-KVCaMxgp
SUMMARY:Tribute to David Boerner's Legacy
DTSTAMP:20260306T012151Z
DTSTART:20260311T230000Z
DESCRIPTION:Please join us for a Celebration of David Boerner's Life & Lega
	cy in Sullivan Hall on March 11th from 4:00 PM to 6:30 PM.  The event will
	 feature opportunities to share how Dave's legacy impacted you as well as 
	a chance to reconnect with those he similarly influenced.\n\n \n\nWhether 
	or not you are able to attend the event in person\, please consider submit
	ting a short note \\(with an image\, if available\\) through this link: ht
	tps://www.kudoboard.com/boards/9GUiGziW.  We will display the notes from t
	his board on a looping slideshow during the event.\n\n \n\nAn excerpt from
	 Dave's obituary:\n\n \n\nOn March 9\, 2025\, the legal profession lost an
	 icon when former King County Chief Deputy Criminal Prosecutor and Profess
	or David Boerner\, 85\, passed away peacefully in Mercer Island\, Washingt
	on. David followed his beloved wife\, Barbara\, who passed just three mont
	hs before him.\n\n \n\nA distinguished prosecutor\, professor\, legal scho
	lar\, and champion of social justice\, Dave was a mentor\, educator\, advo
	cate\, father\, grandfather\, and loving husband whose impact will be felt
	 for generations.\n\n \n\nAs a prosecutor\, Dave helped modernize Washingt
	on's legal system\, played a key role on the Norm Maleng-led taskforce tha
	t shaped the Community Protection Act and the Sexually Violent Predators S
	tatute\, spearheaded the Sentencing Guidelines Commission\, and advised th
	e state Supreme Court\, Bar Association\, and other judicial bodies. His c
	ontributions earned widespread state and national recognition\, cementing 
	his legacy as a leader in criminal justice reform.\n\n \n\nAs a professor\
	, Dave was deeply committed to professional integrity\, teaching courses i
	n criminal law\, criminal procedure\, evidence\, and professional responsi
	bility. One of his most enduring contributions was co-founding the Academi
	c Resource Center's Access Admission Program\, where he helped more than 1
	\,000 aspiring lawyers overcome barriers to legal education\, fostering a 
	more diverse and just profession. His students didn't just gain legal know
	ledge — they carried forward his unwavering commitment to ethics\, equity\
	, and justice.\n\n \n\nDave Boerner exemplified the highest values of his 
	profession — humanity\, humility\, excellence\, ethics\, integrity\, and a
	dvocacy. His unwavering passion for justice and education left an indelibl
	e mark on the legal community and on the careers of so many who have reach
	ed out after his passing. He will be remembered by all for his dedication 
	to making the criminal justice system more just.\n\n \n\nHe is survived by
	: his children Judy\, Dan\, and Rich\, and their spouses\; six grandchildr
	en\; colleagues\; students\; and a grateful legal profession that will car
	ry forward his legacy. Dave's children deeply mourn the recent passing of 
	both their parents but they take comfort in knowing that Dave and Barb are
	 together again in their final Pleasant Valley resting place.\n\n \n\nIf y
	ou have any questions about the event\, please reach out to Karsten Kohout
	: kohoutk@seattleu.edu.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/t
	ribute-to-david-boerner-s-legacy/18260236/2026-03-11T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday -
	 All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/tribute-to-david-boerner-
	s-legacy/18260236/2026-03-11T00
LOCATION:Sullivan Hall\, 2nd Floor Gallery\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H30M
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:mbwAOgGJaBPXMAL1qZ7Z2
SUMMARY:Wellness Wednesday Astrology Readings with Stephanie Gailing
DTSTAMP:20260306T012151Z
DTSTART:20260311T230000Z
DESCRIPTION:Stephanie Gailing\, Cloud Room's in-house Astrologer\, is offer
	ing Cloud Room Members complimentary 1-on-1 astrology readings and insight
	s via zoom! With over 20 years of professional experience\, Stephanie Gail
	ing weaves together astrological insights\, compassion-based coaching\, an
	d family constellations to provide her clients with stellar life guidance.
	 The author of seven books on wellness and astrology\, Stephanie is also t
	he co-host of the So Divine! Podcast. Her work has been featured in Vogue\
	, MindBodyGreen\, Well \\+ Good\, New Day Northwest\, The Seattle Times\, 
	and other outlets. Make sure to sign up for a 15 minute session while they
	're available.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/wellness-w
	ednesday-astrology-readings-with-stephanie-gailing/18061648/2026-03-11T00\
	n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/wellness-wednesday-astrol
	ogy-readings-with-stephanie-gailing/18061648/2026-03-11T00
LOCATION:The Cloud Room\, 1424 11th Ave Suite 400\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
